            "answer_text": "The Apple Watch requires an iPhone 5s or newer in order to go through the set up process, and an Apple Watch equipped with 4G connectivity will require at least an iPhone 6. Unfortunately, the Watch app is not available for the iPad, so you will definitely need an iPhone in order to properly use the Apple Watch. The Near Future The Apple Watch\u2019s biggest leap toward independence from the iPhone may be driven by the new wireless 5G standard. With the conversion from 4G to 5G will offer much improved network latency, and allow the iWatch to be a stand-alone device. ",
